    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-burrito-bowl-with-tomato-salsa-and-chipotle-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (reserve some leaves for a garnish!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-burrito-bowl-with-tomato-salsa-and-chipotle-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>diced shallot</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> in a small bowl with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-burrito-bowl-with-tomato-salsa-and-chipotle-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong> and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> to a large bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>mayo</strong> in a separate bowl and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>chipotle mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-burrito-bowl-with-tomato-salsa-and-chipotle-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> cornflour</strong> and <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> on a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Firmly press your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> into the cornflour mixture, making sure to evenly coat on both sides \u2013 this is your <strong>coated cod</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-burrito-bowl-with-tomato-salsa-and-chipotle-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated cod</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy cod</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-burrito-bowl-with-tomato-salsa-and-chipotle-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>seasoned brown rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-cod-burrito-bowl-with-tomato-salsa-and-chipotle-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>seasoned brown rice</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Top with<strong> </strong>the <strong>tomato salsa</strong>, <strong>pickled slaw</strong> and <strong>crispy cod</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>chipotle mayo </strong>and garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
